rComments: A lot of reading the lecture slides and very dry but the course material is dry since it's an introductory course. Very vague guidelines and specific expectations. Cheatsheet will save your life, but you're going to need to know a lot of random facts and highly specific details. Very nice lady though.

I can tell she is super nice BUT honestly the most boring lectures ever! Made learning difficult, especially as she just reads off the slides. Rarely give meaningful real life examples/applications, which would have many financial concepts MUCH easier to understand

The B in Boyko stands for boring... Shes literally just so monotone you cant even manage to pay attention for the 2 hours a week that you have to suffer through the class. There are way better profs for 230 but if you do get stuck with her its not a big deal. The prof doesnt really matter for the course. Just know the lecture slides.
Not the best prof but way better than Bing Han (who teaches the course during the other term). Lectures can be pretty boring.
Lectures are straightforward but can be really boring at times. She is caring and knowledgeable.

She's really rude and inconsiderate. Lectures are so boring as she just reads off the slides. Not very helpful when you have any questions after class. Just wants to get paid, do the bare minimum, and leave type of prof.

-Provided little to no constructive feedback on assignments -Her favourite line when she messes up on grading is "Life is unfair". -She uses exact questions from past mid-terms and selects a different answer for MC to screw with students -Emailing her for a question or clarifications will result in either "Can't tell your" or "Ask someone else"
Quite boring lecturer that reads off of powerpoint slides. Covers a lot in each class. But the slides are great and packed with information and becomes a great study tool for the test/exam.
